<TITLE> Proshika boss faces laundering charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 3 (bdnews24.com)The Anticorruption Commission is set to press charges against Proshika chairman Kazi Faruq Ahmed and his son Rubayet Ahmed in a money laundering case, a top ACC official said Monday. Director general (admin) Col Hanif Iqbal, in an ACC weekly briefing, said the commission had approved the charge sheet against the NGO boss and his son for misappropriation and illegal transactions involving Tk 1.03 crore belonging to the Proshika Computer System Trust. The commission has also approved a case against Liberal Democratic Party secretary general Prof Jahanara Begum, who was formerly an adviser to the four-party alliance government, for possession of illegal wealth and suppression of wealth-related information. Jahanara faces charges of amasssing Tk 2.03 crore beyond known sources of income and concealing information on assets of Tk 2 crore. bdnew
